=============================================

Introduction
Hello, good morning! My name is Girish Gajanan Pote. I live in Mulund, Mumbai. I have completed my Bachelor’s degree in Engineering from Saraswati College of Engineering, Kharghar.
Currently, I work at Capgemini as an Associate Consultant, and I have 4 years of experience in Java Production Support in Banking financial services domain.
At present, working on project HDFC Bank – Card Business Customer Interface. This is an internal Java web application used by the HDFC call center team to handle customer credit card queries such as loan applications, disbursements, EMI setups, dispute management, and more.
Project Details:

Technology: Java 8, Spring MVC 5.1.5
Database: Oracle and VisionPlus (Mainframe)
Integration: Data fetched from VisionPlus via MQ (Messaging Queue)
Servers: 12 JVMs distributed across 4 servers, deployed on WAS (WebSphere Application Server)
Load Balancing: Implemented using Netscaler

My Responsibilities:

Fix production issues and bugs based on priority
Monitor application logs and share important reports with clients
Deploy WAR files on WAS servers (UAT)
Run CI/CD pipelines after new commits
Generate and share Sonar reports
Check for vulnerabilities, fix code bugs and code smells
Monitor CPU utilization
Maintain documentation for production issues
Assist developers with writing JUnit tests, creating JSP pages, adding new UI elements, and writing DB queries

Additionally, I successfully led and completed a Disaster Recovery (DR) drill mandated by RBI guidelines within tight deadlines, ensuring minimal downtime and high application availability. The client appreciated our efforts.
